# EduGuardian 2.0 – Implementation Plan

> AI-Powered Anti-Cheating Proctoring System (Offline + Online)

## Overview

Build a complete anti-cheating platform with: React frontend (client-side AI), Spring Boot backend (REST + WebSocket + JWT), Python AI microservice (ONNX/Whisper), and MySQL database. The system supports both offline and online proctoring.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Frontend["React Frontend (Vite)"]
        UI[Dashboard UI] --> WS_C[WebSocket Client]
        UI --> AI_C[Client-side AI - TensorFlow.js]
        UI --> IDB[IndexedDB - Offline Storage]
        AI_C --> CAM[WebRTC Camera/Mic]
    end
    subgraph Backend["Spring Boot Backend"]
        API[REST Controllers] --> SVC[Services]
        WSS[WebSocket Server] --> SVC
        SVC --> REPO[JPA Repositories]
        SVC --> JWT[JWT Auth]
        SVC --> PDF[PDF Generator]
        SVC --> BC[Blockchain Logger]
        REPO --> DB[(MySQL)]
    end
    subgraph AI["Python AI Service (FastAPI)"]
        YOLO[YOLOv8-tiny ONNX]
        WHISP[Whisper-tiny]
        OCV[OpenCV Motion]
        RISK[Risk Fusion Engine]
    end
    Frontend -->|REST/WS| Backend
    Backend -->|HTTP| AI
```

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Database Layer

#### [NEW] [schema.sql](file:///S:/EDUGUARD/database/schema.sql)
Full MySQL schema with 9 tables: `users`, `exams`, `proctor_logs`, `audio_events`, `visual_events`, `system_alerts`, `risk_scores`, `device_logs`, `attendance`. Includes indexes, triggers for auto-logging, and a stored procedure for risk aggregation.

---

### 2. Spring Boot Backend

#### [MODIFY] [pom.xml](file:///S:/EDUGUARD/BACKEND/EDUGARD/pom.xml)
Add dependencies: `jjwt` (JWT), `spring-boot-starter-websocket`, `pdfbox`, `jackson`, `validation`.

#### [MODIFY] [application.properties](file:///S:/EDUGUARD/BACKEND/EDUGARD/src/main/resources/application.properties)
Configure MySQL, JWT secret, CORS, server port.

#### [NEW] Entity Models (8 files)
`User.java`, `Exam.java`, `ProctorLog.java`, `AudioEvent.java`, `VisualEvent.java`, `SystemAlert.java`, `RiskScore.java`, `DeviceLog.java` in `com.example.EDUGARD.entity`.

#### [NEW] Repositories (8 files)
JPA repositories for all entities in `com.example.EDUGARD.repository`.

#### [NEW] DTOs
Request/response DTOs: `AuthRequest`, `AuthResponse`, `ExamDTO`, `RiskScoreDTO`, etc. in `com.example.EDUGARD.dto`.

#### [NEW] Security Layer (4 files)
- `JwtUtil.java` – token generation/validation
- `JwtAuthFilter.java` – request filter
- `SecurityConfig.java` – Spring Security config
- `UserDetailsServiceImpl.java` – custom user details

#### [NEW] Controllers (5 files)
- `AuthController.java` – login/register
- `ExamController.java` – CRUD exams
- `ProctorController.java` – proctor logs, events
- `StudentController.java` – student-facing endpoints
- `AdminController.java` – analytics, reports

#### [NEW] Services (6 files)
- `AuthService.java`, `ExamService.java`, `ProctorService.java`
- `RiskScoreService.java` – risk calculation engine
- `PdfReportService.java` – PDF generation via PDFBox
- `BlockchainService.java` – tamper-proof event chain

#### [NEW] WebSocket (2 files)
- `WebSocketConfig.java` – STOMP configuration
- `ProctorWebSocketHandler.java` – real-time event push

