## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
Since this is a greenfield project, verification focuses on:
1. **Backend compilation**: `cd S:\EDUGUARD\BACKEND\EDUGARD && mvnw.cmd compile` – verifies all Java code compiles
2. **Frontend build**: `cd S:\EDUGUARD\EDUGUARDFRONTEND && npm run build` – verifies React app builds without errors
3. **SQL validation**: Load `schema.sql` into MySQL to verify syntax

### Manual Verification
1. **Start frontend dev server** (`npm run dev`) and verify in browser:
   - Login page renders with dark/light theme toggle
   - Student exam page shows webcam preview
   - Invigilator dashboard renders with charts/heatmap
   - Admin dashboard shows analytics components
2. **Visual inspection of all pages** using the browser tool to verify premium UI quality

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a massive system (~60+ files). The AI models (YOLO, Whisper, MediaPipe) require their model files to be downloaded separately—the code includes download instructions and graceful fallbacks. Full end-to-end testing requires a running MySQL instance and model files.
